3. How to Deploy to PROD through GitHub
Once your code is in GitHub, follow these steps in your Snowflake PROD account to deploy it:
1.	Set up Git Integration: Follow the official Snowflake Git setup to create a Secret (for your GitHub token) and an API Integration.
2.	Create Git Repository Object: Run the following SQL to link Snowflake to your repo:
sql
CREATE OR REPLACE GIT REPOSITORY prod_github_repo
  API_INTEGRATION = my_git_api_int
  GIT_CREDENTIALS = my_github_secret
  ORIGIN = 'https://github.com';
Use code with caution.
3.	Deploy the PROD App: Use the "Create from repository" option in the Snowsight UI.
1.	Go to Projects > Streamlit.
2.	Click the dropdown next to + Streamlit and select Create from repository.
3.	Select your prod_github_repo, the main branch, and your streamlit_app.py file.
4.	Automate Updates: Whenever you push changes to GitHub, run ALTER GIT REPOSITORY prod_github_repo FETCH; in Snowflake to pull the latest version into your production app. 
